        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 22 at 4:36PM EDT by NWS Wakefield VA</headline>
        <description>At 435 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Gaston, or near Dahlia, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Dahlia around 440 PM EDT.
Claresville around 450 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Adams Grove, Grizzard,
Gum Forks, Lanes Corner, Bryants Corner, Slates Corner, Pleasant
Hill, Mason, Severn, and Margarettsville.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
